# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PUBLIC-REPO SAFETY  ·  University of Melbourne Biology Tutor
# Everything here is kept OUT of the published repo to protect copyright (UoM
# lecture material) and the private reasoning layer. Only original rewrites
# (vault/concepts, vault/topics) and the pipeline code are published.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# 1) Copyright sources — UoM lecture material, extraction-only, NEVER committed
raw/
*.pdf
*.pptx
*.ppt
*.docx

# 2) Converted intermediates that still contain copyright lecture text
md/                 # lecture PDFs converted to markdown (= the slides as text)
md-questions/       # review docs converted to markdown

# 3) CORE ALGORITHM / IP — the 4C verification engine is NOT published.
#    Design principles are documented in README; the implementation stays private.
verify/             # 4C verifier + stitcher + Prolog rules (verify.py, stitch.py, wiki.pl)
*.pl

# 4) Review questions: AI-generated, kept private (publish:false by design).
#    Excluded from the PUBLIC repo; they still ship to the private HF agent.
vault/questions/

# 5) Misc
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.env
.DS_Store
.obsidian/workspace*
